'''apoapsis''' (''plural'' '''apoapsides''')

#(''astronomy'') The [[point]] of a [[body]]'s [[ellipse|elliptical]] [[orbit]] about the [[system]]'s [[centre]] of [[mass]] where the [[distance]] between the body and the centre of mass is at its [[maximum]]. For some [[celestial]] bodies, specialised terms are used: see [[w:en:Apsis|Apsis (Wikipedia)]] for details.

